 number of topics, including agreements reached in Copenhagen and Cancun, ocean warming and increased acidity, the economic impact of climate change, and advantages gained by communities and business from adapting to climate change. The extensive maps and graphics have been updated with new data, making this edition once again an essential resource for everyone concerned with this pressing subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aClimatic changesvCharts, diagrams, etc. 0aClimatic changesvMaps. 0aClimatic changes. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Meteorology & Climatology.2bisacsh  aaction.  aactivist.  aadaptation.  aadapting.  aatlas.  acancun.  aclimate agreements.  aclimate change.  acommunity.  acopenhagen.  aeconomy.  aemissions.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental degredation.  aenvironmentalism.  aglobal.  ahealth and wellness.  ahealth impacts.  ainternational.  anatural disasters.  anatural world.  aocean warming.  apollution.  apublic health.  arenewable energy.  aresearch.  avulnerable populations.  avulnerable.  awarning signs.  aweather.  aworldwide.1 aCousteau, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowning, Thomas E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMaathai, Wangari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052026823440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096682640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966826423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966826/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-